{"type":"message","id":"11aa7b03","parentId":"41b2ce99","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:18:54.008Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ckc6jej7kclx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and what action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- The big pending item is the **TIC Experiment** (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe insight from this session is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC experiment needs to:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be the most concrete, specific action to advance this. I should:\r\n\r\n1. First, understand the current pulse logs structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's already a TIC implementation started. Looking at the notes, I see references to `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` but I don't see a TIC implementation file yet.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to:\r\n- Create a TIC classifier script that can analyze the pulse logs\r\n- Or update the research doc with a concrete implementation plan\r\n- Or create the initial TIC experiment code\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction, I should create or modify files. Let me create the TIC experiment implementation.\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implements the invariance detection algorithm\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant/variant\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is the most direct path to the pending action.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. The pulse logs contain the data needed, but no TIC classifier implementation exists yet. A concrete implementation is needed before classification accuracy can be measured.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant vs variant content, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Experiment: Test causal-compression duality hypothesis\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,  # Analyze last N pulses\r\n    [float]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSScriptRoot -Parent) -Parent\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$LogDir = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"logs\"\r\n$PulseLogs = Get-ChildItem $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($PulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content hashes for each pulse\r\n$PulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $PulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $hash = (Get-FileHash -InputStream ([System.IO.MemoryStream]::new([System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($content)))).Hash\r\n    $PulseData += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Hash = $hash\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Time = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build n-gram vocabulary from all pulses\r\n$AllText = ($PulseData | ForEach-Object { $_.Content }) -join \" \"\r\n$Words = [regex]::Matches($AllText, '\\b\\w{4,}\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.ToLower() }\r\n$WordCounts = $Words | Group-Object -NoElement | Sort-Object Count -Descending\r\n\r\n# Identify INVARIANTS: terms appearing in >= threshold% of pulses\r\n$InvariantTerms = @()\r\n$VariantTerms = @()\r\nforeach ($group in $WordCounts) {\r\n    $Term = $group.Name\r\n    $DocFreq = ($PulseData | Where-Object { $_.Content -like \"*$Term*\" }).Count / $PulseData.Count\r\n    if ($DocFreq -ge $InvarianceThreshold) {\r\n        $InvariantTerms += $Term\r\n    } else {\r\n        $VariantTerms += $Term\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Results ---\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariant terms found: $($InvariantTerms.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variant terms found: $($VariantTerms.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariant/variant ratio per pulse\r\n$ClassificationResults = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $PulseData.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $current = $PulseData[$i]\r\n    $next = $PulseData[$i + 1]\r\n    \r\n    $currentWords = [regex]::Matches($current.Content, '\\b\\w{4,}\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.ToLower() } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    $nextWords = [regex]::Matches($next.Content, '\\b\\w{4,}\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.ToLower() } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    \r\n    $invariantsInCurrent = ($currentWords | Where-Object { $_ -in $InvariantTerms }).Count\r\n    $variantsInCurrent = ($currentWords | Where-Object { $_ -in $VariantTerms }).Count\r\n    $total = $currentWords.Count\r\n    \r\n    $invariantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $invariantsInCurrent / $total } else\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:18:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325934006}}
